    "# IATO Architecture — Formal Proof Sketch and PoC Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook presents a **formal proof sketch** establishing why the IATO architecture exhibits stable convergence, controlled uncertainty, and empirically aligned risk behavior. All arguments are expressed as mathematical relations and system invariants suitable for audit and regulatory review."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Entropy as a Governed State Variable (Proof Sketch)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Definition**\n",
    "$$H(I) = -\sum_i p_i \log p_i$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Entropy is treated as a **state variable** of the inference system, not a passive diagnostic.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Batch-Level Sensitivity**\n",
    "$$\frac{dH}{d\theta} = -\sum_i \frac{dp_i}{d\theta}(\log p_i + 1)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Control Law**\n",
    "$$|\nabla_\theta H| \le \epsilon_H \Rightarrow \text{Autonomous inference}$$\n",
    "$$|\nabla_\theta H| > \epsilon_H \Rightarrow \text{Throttling or Human Review}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Audit Invariant**\n",
    "$$H_t \prec H_{t+1} \Rightarrow \exists\; \text{serialized control event}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Analytical Stability of the PoC\n",
    "\n",
    "**Claim**: The PoC exhibits stable convergence and reproducible stochastic behavior.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Justification**\n",
    "$$\mathbb{E}[\Delta H_t] \le 0 \quad \text{under bounded curvature}$$\n",
    "$$\lambda_{\max}(\nabla^2 \mathcal{L}) \le \Lambda \Rightarrow \text{No runaway updates}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Thus, entropy is governed, stability is enforced analytically, and learning remains auditable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Pareto Optimisation as an Economic Proof Layer\n",
    "\n",
    "**Multi-Objective Surface**\n",
    "$$\max \; \text{EKR}(t, H, c)$$\n",
    "subject to:\n",
    "$$TP \uparrow, \quad C_{fraud} \downarrow, \quad C_{op} \le C_{max}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pareto Frontier Definition**\n",
    "$$\nexists (x',y') : x' \ge x \land y' \ge y \land (x',y') \neq (x,y)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Empirical Optimum**\n",
    "$$\text{EKR}_{max} = 90.0194 \;\text{at}\; (t=10, H=0.6, c=0.02)$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Hierarchical and Correlated Monte Carlo Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pipeline**\n",
    "$$\text{Pareto} \rightarrow \text{HP-MC} \rightarrow \text{CMC}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Hierarchical Monte Carlo invalidates regimes that appear optimal under independence assumptions but fail under correlated uncertainty.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Latent Dependency Parameter**\n",
    "$$r_{latent} \in [0,1]$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Failure Probability**\n",
    "$$P_{majority} = P\left(\sum X_i > \frac{n}{2}\right)$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Correlation Gap — Formal Risk Argument\n",
    "\n",
    "**Naive Binomial**\n",
    "$$P_{bin} = \binom{n}{k} p^k (1-p)^{n-k}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Assumes independence: \(\rho = 0\).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Empirical Correlation**\n",
    "$$P_{corr,emp} = \frac{succ}{trials}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Rho-Matched Beta–Binomial**\n",
    "$$P_{bb,\rho} = \binom{n}{k} \frac{B(k+\alpha', n-k+\beta')}{B(\alpha',\beta')}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Risk Inflation Bound**\n",
    "$$P_{bb,\rho} \gg P_{bin} \quad \text{when} \; r_{latent} > 0$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Empirical Proof via Majority Failure Example\n",
    "\n",
    "**Parameters**\n",
    "$$n = 11, \quad p = 0.02$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Theoretical (Independent)**\n",
    "$$P_{majority} \approx 2.71 \times 10^{-8}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Correlated Reality**\n",
    "$$r_{latent} = 0.5 \Rightarrow P_{emp} = 0.00585$$\n",
    "\n",
    "This discontinuity constitutes a **constructive proof** of the correlation gap."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Purpose of Each Method (Formal Mapping)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pareto Optimisation**\n",
    "$$\Rightarrow \text{Efficiency frontier under skewed distributions}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Hierarchical Probabilistic MC**\n",
    "$$\Rightarrow \text{Bayesian uncertainty propagation}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Correlated / Causal MC**\n",
    "$$\Rightarrow \text{Empirical validation of } \rho_{emp} \approx \rho_{model}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
